comments.message:
You're holding around a pointer in every instance of this class because you're trying to invent your own RTTI?

At a minimum this should be added to the vtable:

    virtual std::string_view eventName() const = 0;

Even better is if you have:

template <typename T>
struct NamedBasicEvent : BasicEvent
{
   //...
};

Where the NamedBasicEvent is a CRTP that uses techniques such as this to turn it into a constexpr function: https://bitwizeshift.github.io/posts/2021/03/09/getting-an-unmangled-type-name-at-compile-time/

Ideally you can just do "struct RegisterDbusEvent : public NamedBasicEvent<RegisterDbusEvent>" and the name registration happens by the compiler.
